The key to this problem is how to count the number of apples on the region we want to cut.

We can simply use the prefix sum that help to identify the number of apples between any two index.

Therefore, we need to pre-process the input array, get the prefix sum horizatonally and vertically.

With the prefix sum array, we can create a dp funtion that get the number of cuts in the region (i, j) to (row - 1, col - 1)


